  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="meta">Effective date: 3 April 2026 · MarketKit by Hadi Irwein · <a href="mailto:hadi@eiilab.com">hadi@eiilab.com</a> · See also: <a href="/terms.html">Terms of Use</a></p>

  <div class="summary-box">
    <p><strong>Plain-English Summary</strong><br>
    MarketKit does not track you, sell your data, or store anything about you on its servers. Everything you type into the tool stays in your browser. The only external data exposure comes from standard CDN requests (Google Fonts, Cloudflare, jsDelivr) and the URL Shortener feature which sends your URL to TinyURL. A cookie notice is shown on your first visit to acknowledge this minimal exposure. That's it.</p>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
    <p>MarketKit is operated by Hadi Irwein, trading as eiilab, based in Singapore. For privacy-related enquiries, contact <a href="mailto:hadi@eiilab.com">hadi@eiilab.com</a>.</p>
    <p>This Privacy Policy applies to the MarketKit website, including the main toolkit, the <a href="/tools.html">Recommended Tools</a> page, the <a href="/terms.html">Terms of Use</a>, and this Privacy Policy page.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. What Data Is Collected and Why</h2>
    <p>The table below summarises every data point that may be collected or exposed when you use MarketKit.</p>
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Data type</th>
        <th>Source</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
        <th>Stored by MarketKit?</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>IP address, browser type, referring URL</td>
        <td>Cloudflare Pages (hosting) and Cloudflare CDN</td>
        <td>Security, DDoS protection, server access logs</td>
        <td>No — held by Cloudflare per their policy</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>IP address, browser type</td>
        <td>Google Fonts CDN</td>
        <td>Font delivery; Google may log requests</td>
        <td>No — held by Google per their policy</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>IP address, browser type</td>
        <td>jsDelivr CDN</td>
        <td>QR library delivery; standard access logs</td>
        <td>No — held by jsDelivr per their policy</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>The URL you enter</td>
        <td>TinyURL API (URL Shortener tab only)</td>
        <td>Generating a shortened link on your request</td>
        <td>No — sent to TinyURL's servers only</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>UTM lists, campaign names</td>
        <td>Settings tab — browser <code>localStorage</code></td>
        <td>Persisting your preferences between sessions</td>
